SELECT DISTINCT 0 as id, head AS label FROM edges
UNION
SELECT DISTINCT 0 as id, tail AS label FROM edges

SELECT ts, head, relation, tail
FROM edges
WHERE ts < 2005

SELECT ts, head, relation, tail
FROM edges
WHERE ts >= 2005 and ts < 2015

SELECT ts, head, relation, tail
FROM edges
WHERE ts >= 2015

SELECT 
    ts,
    COUNT(*) as count
FROM edges_sampled

GROUP BY ts
ORDER BY ts

FROM edges

FROM edges
